---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Mentoring | Motunrayo Koyejo" 
  currentPage="mentoring"
>
  <header style="padding: 80px 0 20px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">Mentoring</div>
      <h1>Helping more women <em>break in</em>.</h1>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section style="padding: 20px 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>When I was starting out, I cobbled together a career from advice that wasn't really meant for me. The engineers I followed were brilliant. I learned enormously from them, but they were mostly men, mostly from other places, and the specific friction I was facing didn't show up in their stories. So every problem took longer than it needed to. Every milestone felt harder-won than it maybe had to be. I figured it out eventually, but I thought the whole time: <em>there should be someone doing this for someone like me</em>.</p>
        <p>Now I am that someone. Since 2024, I've mentored women through three structured programs, plus plenty of informal 1:1s, and helped more than a dozen of them land their first engineering roles. The ones who were ready just needed someone to believe they were. Some of the best messages I've ever received came from those women.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-card">
        <p class="quote-text">"Motunrayo's guidance was nothing short of transformative. Her belief in me propelled my career to new heights."</p>
        <div class="quote-attr">Soni Mwangi · now at H.E.R. DAO</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Where I <em>show up</em></h2>
      <div class="mentor-programs">
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">Wentors</div>
          <div class="program-desc">IWD WE-DISCOVER Cohort · 2024</div>
          <div class="program-detail">Mentored three women through a seven-week program covering technical skills, CV prep, and interview readiness. All three are now working software engineers, including one who sent a thank-you note I'm not going to stop mentioning.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">HerSynergy × TechHer</div>
          <div class="program-desc">Structured Mentorship · 2024–25</div>
          <div class="program-detail">Worked 1:1 with two mentees over three months on technical foundations and career strategy. Both landed software engineering roles at African tech companies.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">She Code Africa × Glovo</div>
          <div class="program-desc">Women in Tech Bootcamp · 2025</div>
          <div class="program-detail">Selected as a backend mentor for a 12-week program teaching 100 women to code. Guided three mentees through Node.js curriculum and their final projects.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">Mentoring Club</div>
          <div class="program-desc">Ongoing · 1:1 sessions</div>
          <div class="program-detail">Open mentorship through the Mentoring Club platform, mostly early-career backend engineers and career-switchers finding their footing.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Who I'm <em>actually useful to</em></h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>My mentorship lands best with <strong>early-career women in tech</strong>, especially the ones moving into backend or transitioning from another career entirely. It's where my experience is most directly relevant. The specific questions of "how do I get in" and "how do I stay in without burning out or quitting" are ones I've thought hard about and have real opinions on.</p>
        <p>The questions I hear most often:</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mentor-programs" style="margin-top: 16px;">
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">Backend fundamentals</div>
          <div class="program-detail">What to learn, in what order, and how to know when you actually know something.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">API design & systems thinking</div>
          <div class="program-detail">Moving from "I can write endpoints" to "I can design systems that scale."</div>
        </div>
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">Technical interview prep</div>
          <div class="program-detail">How to actually prepare, what to practise, and how not to unravel under pressure.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="program">
          <div class="program-name">Career navigation</div>
          <div class="program-detail">The unwritten stuff: visibility, advocating for yourself, staying confident in rooms where you're often the only one who looks like you.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="cta-band">
        <h3>Looking for a mentor?</h3>
        <p>If you're an early-career woman in tech, especially in backend, I'd love to hear from you. Tell me a little about where you are, what you're working on, and what's in your way.</p>
        <a class="cta-btn" href="https://www.mentoring-club.com/profiles/motunrayo-koyejo#mentor-profile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a call</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>